    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.37"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">37</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="italics">Clay Center Public Schools</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    ==================================================
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">CLAY CENTER, NEBRASKA 68933
                        <lb/>
                    TELEPHONE 402-762-4485
                        <lb/>
                        
                    SAM TOWNSEND 
                        <lb/>
                    SUPERINTENDENT
                        <lb/>
                    
                    DICK CHOCHON
                        <lb/>
                    HIGH SCHOOL PRINCIPAL
                        <lb/>
                    MRS. REBECCA HAJNY
                        <lb/>
                    ELEMENTARY PRINCIPAL</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 18, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>% Julius <hi rend="caps">D.</hi> Young</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska  68505</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </opener>
                <p>Last August at Bancroft I spoke to you about the possibility of bringing a class to visit Dr. Neihardt. We usually take our field trips in the spring and so that time is arriving again. Before definitely scheduling the trip, I would like to know the nature of the visit. Would it take the form of a lecture by Dr. Neihardt? Or would it be a question and answer session? Personally I would prefer a lecture and display session, with perhaps some questions from the sutdents at the end. How long would the session be? What is the cost? I believe you mentioned the best time would be 2 p.m. In case we would have to come in the morning, is there a preferred time? I would appreciate hearing from you soon with the answers to my questions. Then I will, after receiving administration approval, contact you regarding a date.</p> 
                
                <p>Kind regards to you and to Dr. Neihardt.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Lamont Larson</signed> 
                    <signed>Lamont Larson</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Clay Center High School</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Clay Center, Nebraska   68933</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
